From: Eason <30045503+Eason0729@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sun, 3 May 2026 00:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 11/11] Increase mmc_spi CRC retry count to 100

Increase the CRC retry count for SPI MMC transfers from 5 to 100.
This provides more tolerance for intermittent SPI bus errors on
wiring with marginal signal integrity, preventing the MMC core
from falsely declaring the card as removed after exhausting retries.

Signed-off-by: 邱繼叡 Eason CHIU <30045503+Eason0729@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 drivers/mmc/host/mmc_spi.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/mmc/host/mmc_spi.c b/drivers/mmc/host/mmc_spi.c
index deb39fc80..b9e20753f 100644
--- a/drivers/mmc/host/mmc_spi.c
+++ b/drivers/mmc/host/mmc_spi.c
@@ -898,7 +898,7 @@
 {
 	struct mmc_spi_host	*host = mmc_priv(mmc);
 	int			status = -EINVAL;
-	int			crc_retry = 5;
+	int			crc_retry = 100;
 	struct mmc_command	stop;
 
 #ifdef DEBUG
